  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lifesaving Shelter/NFI Provision to Conflict-Affected IDPs in Afar, Amhara and Tigray</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The CERF intervention is supporting households in Amhara, Afar and Tigray regions of Ethiopia through provision of life-saving emergency shelter and non-food items (NFI) support (in-kind as well as cash) for a period of six months. The response under this project includes the rapid provision of emergency shelter and NFI kits, partitioning of communal shelters to ensure privacy and security of families, upgrading communal shelters to make them habitable and the provision of rental assistance in the form of cash (USD 90, for six months, determined in coordination with the Shelter/NFI Cluster Coordinator), based on need and appropriateness.</narrative>
  </description>
